Message:
Ilya Kabanov  great breakdown. Quick ToS mapping: if a plugin is truly not scraping, it mostly avoids 8.2(2). But you are still in the risk zone if it does any of the following:
- 8.2(13) automates actions or engagement (connect, message, like/comment/share, add or download contacts, redirect messages)
- 8.2(15) overlays or modifies the UI/appearance (injects elements, removes/covers ads, etc.)
- 8.2(14) framing/mirroring or simulating LI appearance/function
- 8.2(3) bypassing access controls or use limits
- 8.2(4) copying/using/distributing info obtained from LI without consent
- 8.2(1) risky auth behavior (cookies, credentials, using another account)

So ‚Äúnot scraping‚Äù is necessary, but not sufficient, if the extension touches automation or UI. Also agree with your point - scanning 5k extension IDs starts to look like fingerprinting at scale. ü§Ø
